JIRA is currently using the 'Delete Issue' permission to control the ManageTrackback link. JIRA should have separate permission for ManageTrackback.

{code:xml|title=view_trackbacks.jsp}
...
		<webwork:if test="/hasIssuePermission('delete', /issue) == true">
		<br>
		<a href="<%=request.getContextPath()%>/secure/ManageTrackbacks.jspa?id=<webwork:property value="id" />"><webwork:text name="'trackback.manage.title'"/></a>
		</webwork:if>
...
{code}

MySQL integration page at http://www.atlassian.com/software/jira/docs/latest/databases/mysql.html in point 3.1 states:
{quote}
The URL above assumes a UTF-8 database - ie. created with create database jiradb character set utf8;. If you don't specify character set utf8 you risk getting 'Data truncation: Data too long for column' errors when importing data. See storing non-ASCII characters in MySQL for details.
{quote}
Although, almost second everyday in SAC there a new case related to the incorrect character encoding used in the JIRA db and characters not supported ASCII or LATIN1 - customers from Asia

I think, this problem originate from our docs, where a "big flashing neon" should print  the above quoted instruction. Basically, some users just don't follow the docs page to the letter. :(

