After another [support case|https://support.atlassian.com/browse/JSP-19195] involving seriously slow Lucene performance caused by virus protection software, can I suggest that we please add a warning, something like the following, to the initial configuration screen and the Administration > Indexing screen of JIRA:

{panel}
Make sure your indexing directory is on a fast local disk. Make sure there is not any virus protection running. Make sure that there is not file compression software running on the indexing directory. See [here|http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Indexing+in+JIRA] for details. 
{panel}

